{%- comment -%}
  youtube-facade-content.liquid                         bd hairmnl-theme-za7u.6

  Post-processor for rich-text HTML (product.description, etc.) that converts
  eager-loading pasted YouTube <iframe> embeds into the theme's existing
  <lite-youtube> click-to-load facade (assets/lite-youtube.js).

  WHY: PDP descriptions containing a pasted YouTube iframe eager-load ~1 MB of
  YouTube on initial page load. loading="lazy" does NOT defer it — the iframe
  sits high in the description (within the browser's lazy threshold) AND theme.js's
  read-more truncate/resize pass re-inserts it via appendChild, forcing the load
  regardless of the lazy attribute (verified by network trace 2026-05-31).
  Replacing the <iframe> with <lite-youtube> (no iframe in the DOM until the
  shopper clicks the poster) eliminates the eager load AND is immune to theme.js
  re-insertion: a re-inserted <lite-youtube> just re-renders its poster image;
  the YouTube embed only loads on click (#activate in assets/lite-youtube.js).

  PARAMS:
    content — the rich-text HTML to process (required)
    alt     — optional alt-text prefix for the poster img (e.g. product.title)

  CALLER CONTRACT: when this snippet's output contains '<lite-youtube', the
  caller must load assets/lite-youtube.js once. The product sections emit the
  standard guarded loader (the same window.__liteYoutubeLoaded pattern used by
  snippets/media.liquid) when product_description_content contains '<lite-youtube'.

  ALGORITHM (Liquid has no regex — split/append chains only, mirroring
  article-content-with-img-dims.liquid):
    1. Split content on '<iframe'. chunk[0] is everything before the first
       iframe (passes through unchanged).
    2. For each subsequent chunk, the opening tag's attributes run up to the
       first '>'. If those attributes contain a youtube.com/embed/ (or
       youtube-nocookie.com/embed/) src, it is a YouTube embed.
    3. Extract the video id from .../embed/VIDEOID?... and emit a 16:9
       padding-top container wrapping a <lite-youtube videoid="...">, then
       append the tail (everything after this iframe's </iframe>).
    4. Non-YouTube iframes (Vimeo, maps, etc.) are reconstructed unchanged.

  LIMITATIONS:
    - Only converts <iframe> embeds whose opening tag carries a youtube
      /embed/ src. youtu.be share links / plain-text URLs are not iframes and
      pass through (they never eager-load anyway).
    - Assumes the YouTube iframe is well-formed with a closing </iframe>
      (always true for Shopify rich-text-editor video embeds).

  MIGRATION-DEBT: bespoke P6 post-processor; will need port to OS 2.0.
  Reason: OS-2.0 has no built-in "pasted-iframe -> facade" hook, and the
  lite-youtube facade itself is already tracked migration debt (epic za7u).
  No-op alternatives (theme setting / app / merchandising) were considered per
  the P6 freeze: the migration-clean option is to move videos into the product
  MEDIA gallery (which already uses this facade), but that needs per-product
  operator action; this snippet makes existing in-description videos performant
  automatically. Port difficulty: easy (self-contained snippet + 1 wiring line).
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign _yt_content = content | default: '' -%}
{%- assign _yt_chunks = _yt_content | split: '<iframe' -%}

{%- if _yt_chunks.size > 1 -%}
  {%- assign _yt_out = _yt_chunks | first -%}
  {%- for _chunk in _yt_chunks offset: 1 -%}
    {%- comment -%} opening tag attributes run from after '<iframe' up to the first '>' {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- assign _open = _chunk | split: '>' | first -%}
    {%- if _open contains 'youtube.com/embed/' or _open contains 'youtube-nocookie.com/embed/' -%}
      {%- comment -%} pull VIDEOID out of .../embed/VIDEOID?params — cut at the first terminator {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- assign _after_embed = _open | split: 'embed/' | last -%}
      {%- assign _vid = _after_embed | split: '?' | first | split: '&' | first | split: '"' | first | split: "'" | first | split: ' ' | first | split: '/' | first | strip -%}
      {%- comment -%} tail = content after this iframe's close (YouTube iframes are empty) {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- assign _tail = _chunk | split: '</iframe>' | last -%}
      {%- if _vid != blank -%}
        {%- capture _facade -%}<div class="lyt-embed-container" style="position:relative;width:100%;max-width:560px;margin:1em auto;padding-top:56.25%;background:#000;"><lite-youtube videoid="{{ _vid }}" params="rel=0&modestbranding=1" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;"><img class="lyt-poster" src="https://i.ytimg.com/vi/{{ _vid }}/hqdefault.jpg" alt="{{ alt | default: 'Product' | strip_html | escape }} video" loading="lazy" fetchpriority="low" width="480" height="360"></lite-youtube></div>{%- endcapture -%}
        {%- assign _yt_out = _yt_out | append: _facade | append: _tail -%}
      {%- else -%}
        {%- comment -%} couldn't parse a video id — leave the original iframe intact {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- assign _yt_out = _yt_out | append: '<iframe' | append: _chunk -%}
      {%- endif -%}
    {%- else -%}
      {%- comment -%} non-YouTube iframe — reconstruct unchanged {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- assign _yt_out = _yt_out | append: '<iframe' | append: _chunk -%}
    {%- endif -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
  {{- _yt_out -}}
{%- else -%}
  {{- _yt_content -}}
{%- endif -%}
